								<h3><span style="color: #3973AC;">CALIPER: Urgent Need for a New Database of Normal Values in Healthy Children</span></h3>
									<p>The care of patients at pediatric health centers is critically dependent on reliable and accurate laboratory tests. Correct interpretation of these tests
									   relies on availability of normal values (a range of blood test results obtained from a group of healthy children to determine what is
									   normal when a child is screened for a disease). By establishing accurate and reliable normal values from a healthy but diverse
									   Canadian paediatric sample population, clinicians and laboratory scientists will be better positioned to accurately diagnose children
									   with medical concerns.</p>									
