								<img src="images/main_body/14623-wgirl_green.gif" alt="Caliper project green girl" border="0" height="157" width="75" align="left" /> 
								</td></tr></table><h3><span style="color: #3973AC;">Benefits of CALIPER</span></h3>
									<p>The major benefit of this project is that it will allow physicians to more accurately interpret children’s test results by comparing patient results to the results obtained from healthy children. This will help them more quickly determine whether or not a child has abnormal levels of a certain blood component and determine the treatment a sick child may need.</p>
									<p>A database of normal values will also prevent misdiagnosis as it will give doctors a more objective means of interpreting results than their personal experience. </p>
									<p>In addition to the benefit of helping sick children across the country and the world, participants are rewarded with $10, 2 community service hours, and the choice between a teddy bear, T-shirt or story book as a thank you for helping. As the participant or any child among their friends or family could get sick at any time, they could personally benefit directly from the results obtained by this study.</p>
